## Repository Exploration Complete

### Documentation Findings
- **Strict markers** enforced via `--strict-markers` in pytest.ini
- **Type hints mandatory** - mypy strict mode in `libs/`, network modules
- **Google-format docstrings required** for public functions
- **Absolute imports only**, specific function imports (`from module import func`)
- **Named arguments required** for calls with >1 argument
- **No single-letter variables**, no dead code, no defensive programming
- **`uv run`** required for all Python/pytest execution
- **Pre-commit + tox** must pass before commits

### Available Utilities (Guest Agent / Windows OS Info)

| Function | Module | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `get_guest_os_info(vmi)` | `utilities.virt` | Polls VMI `guestOSInfo` with 6min timeout until `id` field populated |
| `validate_os_info_vmi_vs_windows_os(vm)` | `utilities.ssp` | Compares VMI guestOSInfo vs actual Windows OS info via SSH |
| `get_windows_os_info(ssh_exec)` | `utilities.ssp` | Gets full OS info dict from Windows guest via PowerShell/SSH |
| `validate_virtctl_guest_agent_data_over_time(vm)` | `utilities.virt` | Validates virtctl guest info stays available over 3min |
| `validate_virtctl_guest_agent_after_guest_reboot(vm, os_type)` | `utilities.virt` | Reboots guest, waits for running, validates agent data |
| `guest_reboot(vm, os_type)` | `utilities.virt` | Stops agent, waits for agent down, reboots guest |
| `wait_for_running_vm(vm, ssh_timeout=TIMEOUT_2MIN, ...)` | `utilities.virt` | Waits for VMI running + SSH |
| `running_vm(vm, ssh_timeout=TIMEOUT_2MIN, ...)` | `utilities.virt` | Starts VM and waits for running |
| `wait_for_user_agent_down(vm, timeout)` | `utilities.virt` | Waits for AgentConnected condition to go False |

**Key constants:** `OS_FLAVOR_WINDOWS = "win"`, `TIMEOUT_30MIN` (for Windows SSH after reboot), timeout constants from `TIMEOUT_1SEC` to `TIMEOUT_180MIN`.

### Common Fixtures (Windows Tests)
- `namespace` (function-scoped) - isolated namespace
- `admin_client` / `unprivileged_client` (session-scoped)
- `windows_os_matrix__class__` - auto-parametrized by `pytest_generate_tests` hook
- `matrix_windows_os_golden_image_data_source` (class-scoped)
- `matrix_windows_os_vm_from_template` (class-scoped) - creates Windows VM from template
- `modern_cpu_for_migration` (session-scoped) - CPU model for Windows VMs

### Test Structure Patterns
- **Module-level markers:** `pytestmark = [pytest.mark.post_upgrade, pytest.mark.special_infra, pytest.mark.high_resource_vm]`
- **Dependency chains:** `TESTS_CLASS_NAME` constant + `@pytest.mark.dependency(name=..., depends=[...])`
- **Polarion IDs:** `@pytest.mark.polarion("CNV-XXXX")` on every test
- **SNO support:** `@pytest.mark.sno` on most tests
- **Class-scoped VM:** All tests in a class share one VM instance

### GRAVEYARD Lessons (10 Entries - Mistakes to AVOID)

1. **HCO CR field casing** - Don't assume camelCase; verify CRD schema
2. **Wrong type hints** - Always use `DynamicClient` for client params, never `object`
3. **Class-scoped VM conflicts** - Never put tests with different VM fixtures in the same class
4. **`run_virtctl_command` stderr** - Always pass `verify_stderr=False` for virtctl commands
5. **`retry_cluster_exceptions` unwraps timeout** - Catch `ApiException`, not `TimeoutExpiredError`
6. **Reset on paused VMI succeeds** - Don't write negative test for this
7. **Unprivileged user has reset permission** - Namespace admin already has VMI subresource perms
8. **SSH timeout after hard reset** - Use `TIMEOUT_10MIN`, not default `TIMEOUT_2MIN`
9. **Paused VMI stays paused after reset** - Don't call `wait_for_running_vm` after reset on paused VMI
10. **`hotplug_spec_vm_and_verify_hotplug` needs migration** - Use `hotplug_spec_vm` on constrained clusters

