### Design Decisions
- **One class, one VM** - follows the exact pattern of `test_windows_os_support.py`, avoids creating multiple expensive Windows VMs
- **Dependency chain** ensures correct ordering: create ‚Üí start ‚Üí info tests ‚Üí reboot ‚Üí agent stop ‚Üí agent start ‚Üí delete
- **Existing utilities reused**: `validate_os_info_vmi_vs_windows_os`, `get_virtctl_os_info`, `validate_virtctl_guest_agent_data_over_time`, `validate_virtctl_guest_agent_after_guest_reboot`, `run_os_command`, `wait_for_user_agent_down`, `get_guest_os_info`
- **GRAVEYARD lessons applied**: no conflicting class-scoped VM fixtures, `verify_stderr` not needed (using existing utility wrappers)

